Jerry:

I guess I&#39;ve been too busy - the bane of the modern world - not to
mention keeping food on the table.  I just now ran across your e-mail
about your single letter practice site, which is linked to the
Read_Alphabet site.  I really like it.  How much trouble would it be to
expand on that idea and add a series of basic words for a beginner to
read?  Might it be practicable if the work could be shared in some
manner by some of our group members?  It seems to me this would be quite
useful for introducing a beginner to the idea of phonemic spelling,
which thinks to the deficiencies of T.O. is, apparently, a totally alien
concept to many.  I like the fact that it gives the individual immediate
feedback.

Paige Gabhart

